<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 12:33:53 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>物理学家开发出测量宇宙膨胀率的新方法</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/physicists-develop-new-method-to-measure-universes-expansion-rate</link><description>几十年来我们都知道宇宙正在膨胀。科学家使用多种技术来测量当今宇宙的膨胀率，即哈勃常数。这些方法是内部一致的，并且基于相同的物理原理，因此哈勃常数的所有观测值都应该一致。但来自早期宇宙数据集的数据与来自晚期宇宙数据集的数据不一致。这个问题被称为哈勃张力，被认为是宇宙学中最重要的开放问题之一。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/physicists-develop-new-method-to-measure-universes-expansion-rate2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 12:33:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/physicists-develop-new-method-to-measure-universes-expansion-rate</guid></item><item><title>微生物为什么要组队？一种新模型解释了波动环境中的养分共享</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/why-do-microbes-team-up-a-new-model-explains-nutrient-sharing-in-fluctuating-environments</link><description>依赖他人来获得你所需要的东西可能会让人感觉是一个冒险的提议——而且也许是一个人性的提议。这实际上是微生物世界中发现的一种生存策略，而且比人们想象的要频繁得多。发现原因是理解微生物如何在医疗、工业和生态环境中形成稳定群落的关键。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-do-microbes-team-up-a-new-model-explains-nutrient-sharing-in-fluctuating-environments3.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 12:18:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/why-do-microbes-team-up-a-new-model-explains-nutrient-sharing-in-fluctuating-environments</guid></item><item><title>当光像大脑一样“思考”时：光子和人工记忆之间的联系</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/when-light-thinks-like-the-brain-the-connection-between-photons-and-artificial-memory</link><description>一项国际研究揭示了量子物理学与人工智能基础理论模型之间令人惊讶的联系。该研究是国家研究委员会纳米技术研究所（Cnr-Nanotec）、意大利理工学院（IIT）、罗马第一大学以及国际研究机构合作的成果。该研究论文近日发表在该杂志上&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/when-light-thinks-like-the-brain-the-connection-between-photons-and-artificial-memory.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 12:03:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/when-light-thinks-like-the-brain-the-connection-between-photons-and-artificial-memory</guid></item><item><title>人工智能为量子物理中的异常实验开发了易于理解的解决方案</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/ai-develops-easily-understandable-solutions-for-unusual-experiments-in-quantum-physics</link><description>图宾根大学的研究人员与一个国际团队合作开发了一种人工智能，可以设计全新的、有时不寻常的量子物理实验，并以研究人员易于理解的方式呈现它们。这包括人类可能从未考虑过的实验设置。新的人工智能不仅仅创建一个单一的设计方案；相反，它编写计算机代码来生成一系列物理实验，即具有相似输出的实验组。该研究已&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-develops-easily-understandable-solutions-for-unusual-experiments-in-quantum-physics.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 11:48:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/ai-develops-easily-understandable-solutions-for-unusual-experiments-in-quantum-physics</guid></item><item><title>二维材料中磁性的电控制有望推动自旋电子学的发展</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/electrical-control-of-magnetism-in-2d-materials-promises-to-advance-spintronics</link><description>传统电子设备利用电子电荷来处理信息。在过去的几十年里，一些电子工程师一直在探索不同类型设备的潜力，这种设备利用电子的固有磁矩（即自旋）来处理和存储数据。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/electrical-control-of-magnetism-in-2d-materials-promises-to-advance-spintronics2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 11:33:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/electrical-control-of-magnetism-in-2d-materials-promises-to-advance-spintronics</guid></item><item><title>为无湍流量子通信扫清道路</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/clearing-the-path-for-turbulence-free-quantum-communication</link><description>渥太华大学的一个团队开发了一种新方法，可以保护自由空间量子密钥分发（QKD）免受大气湍流的影响，大气湍流是通过空气发送量子信息时造成失真和错误的主要原因之一。他们的论文“使用受激参数下转换实现自由空间量子密钥分配的全光湍流缓解” &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/clearing-the-path-for-turbulence-free-quantum-communication3.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 11:18:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/clearing-the-path-for-turbulence-free-quantum-communication</guid></item><item><title>7,000 个 GPU 以前所未有的细节模拟量子微芯片</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/7000-gpus-simulate-quantum-microchip-in-unprecedented-detail</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 11:03:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/7000-gpus-simulate-quantum-microchip-in-unprecedented-detail</guid></item><item><title>韦伯绘制天王星高层大气地图并发现了磁性惊喜</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/webb-maps-uranus-upper-atmosphere-and-finds-a-magnetic-surprise</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 10:48:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/webb-maps-uranus-upper-atmosphere-and-finds-a-magnetic-surprise</guid></item><item><title>天文学家目睹了与“失踪”黑洞有关的前所未有的宇宙爆炸</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/astronomers-witness-unprecedented-cosmic-explosion-linked-to-a-missing-black-hole</link><description>关于虫洞的真相：爱因斯坦的“桥”可能会改写时间本身&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/astronomers-witness-unprecedented-cosmic-explosion-linked-to-a-missing-black-hole.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 10:33:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/astronomers-witness-unprecedented-cosmic-explosion-linked-to-a-missing-black-hole</guid></item><item><title>闪光可以立即构建和消除晶体</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/a-flash-of-light-can-build-and-erase-crystals-instantly</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 10:18:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/a-flash-of-light-can-build-and-erase-crystals-insta